Here, |_âˆ˜_| is the constructor for substitution composition, and the second |_,_| is the constructor for extending a substitution |Ïƒ| with a term |t| of type |A [ Ïƒ ]|.
When formulating the corresponding rule for the interaction between |_âˆ˜_| and |_,_|, we encounter a type mismatch that must be resolved by transport, leading to the well-known \emph{transport hell}:  
